{"title":"Stop ride notice: Shimano issues recall of certain Pro Vibe alloy stems","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/shimano-pro-vibe-alloy-stem-recall","date":1680166319000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/shimano-pro-vibe-alloy-stem-recall\">Stop ride notice: Shimano issues recall of certain Pro Vibe alloy stems</a></p>\n\n<p>Shimano has issued a recall for certain batches of Pro Vibe alloy stems sold since May 2020. Owners are advised to stop using them immediately and complete an identification procedure to check if their stem is one from an affected batch.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>According to Pro, no other stems, including the Vibe Carbon stem, are affected by this issue.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The affected stems can develop corrosion-based cracks at the clamping area of the fork steerer tube, which could lead to the component’s catastrophic failure.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"616\" height=\"296\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Screenshot-2023-03-30-at-08.56.36.png\" alt=\"Pro vibe stem failure\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Screenshot-2023-03-30-at-08.56.36.png 616w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Screenshot-2023-03-30-at-08.56.36-300x144.png 300w\" /><figcaption>Shimano</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Owners of the affected stems are advised to contact the dealer from whom the stem was originally purchased and return it. Dealers will then provide a replacement stem, depending on availability, or offer a refund.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For further information and dealer contact details visit <a href=\"https://www.pro-bikegear.com/uk/news/recall-notice-vibe-stem\" target=\"_blank\">Pro’s recall page</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The affected products are detailed below.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"222\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Screenshot-2023-03-30-at-08.56.28-970x222.png\" alt=\"Pro vibe stem failure list\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Screenshot-2023-03-30-at-08.56.28-970x222.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Screenshot-2023-03-30-at-08.56.28-300x69.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Screenshot-2023-03-30-at-08.56.28-768x176.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Screenshot-2023-03-30-at-08.56.28-750x172.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Screenshot-2023-03-30-at-08.56.28-1140x261.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Screenshot-2023-03-30-at-08.56.28.png 1294w\" /><figcaption>Shimano</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Identification procedure</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Shimano has released a flow diagram as a visual aid to guide users through the mandatory identification procedure, included below, but for the sake of clarity, a written version of the procedure is provided too.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"260\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Screenshot-2023-03-30-at-09.18.22-970x260.png\" alt=\"Pro vibe stem recall procedure\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Screenshot-2023-03-30-at-09.18.22-970x260.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Screenshot-2023-03-30-at-09.18.22-300x80.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Screenshot-2023-03-30-at-09.18.22-768x206.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Screenshot-2023-03-30-at-09.18.22-750x201.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Screenshot-2023-03-30-at-09.18.22-1140x305.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Screenshot-2023-03-30-at-09.18.22.png 1330w\" /><figcaption>Shimano</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"939\" height=\"625\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/PRO-Vibe-stem.png\" alt=\"PRO Vibe stem identification procedure\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/PRO-Vibe-stem.png 939w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/PRO-Vibe-stem-300x200.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/PRO-Vibe-stem-768x511.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/PRO-Vibe-stem-750x499.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/PRO-Vibe-stem-465x310.png 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/PRO-Vibe-stem-620x413.png 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/PRO-Vibe-stem-350x233.png 350w\" /><figcaption>Shimano</figcaption></figure>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/shimano-pro-vibe-alloy-stem-recall\">Stop ride notice: Shimano issues recall of certain Pro Vibe alloy stems</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Sam Challis &#124; Tech Editor","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"e5efffe9a023bd97a164ec33328b895ff083e39c1d2b814f8b73600c46857067","category":"Cycling"}